07/03/2005
TOKYO, Japan -- During a meeting in Tokyo on Friday (4 March), Bosnian Prime Minister Adnan Terzic and his Japanese counterpart, Junichiro Koizumi, agreed to enhance bilateral economic and trade co-operation. Terzic met with government officials, members of parliament and business representatives. Koizumi said Tokyo would continue to support efforts to revive BiH's economy and spur Japanese investment there. 
In other news, Danish Parliament Speaker Christian Mejdahl kicked off a three-day official visit to BiH on Sunday. Mejdahl is expected to meet with senior officials, including Terzic and international community High Representative Paddy Ashdown. (Fena, NTV - 06/03/05; Hayat Fena, Kyodo News - 04/03/05)
